<center><font face='arial'><br><br>





 <b>Ornate/Elemental Armour Quest</b><br><br>Here is a quick guide on how to transform your Ornate/Elemental pattern into the appropiate armour.<br><br>In the Plane of Tranquility, at pos705, neg1735 is a Dwarf called Bor Warhammer. (In the building to the right of the bank)<br><br><br><br>You need to give him 500 platinum (in platinum coins). Make sure you have room for a bag, as he will hand you a container and an emblem.<br><br>In this container, you need to combine the following (no fail, no trivial):<br><br><br> - Your Ornate/Elemental pattern<br> - The emblem<br> - 1-3 Ethereal Silk Swatches*<br><br><br>* 1 swatch for bracers, 2 swatches for boots, arms, cap or gloves, and 3 swatches for legs or robe.<br><br><b>Note:</b> The equivalent of elemental robe is a "Timeless Robe Pattern", which makes a "Timeless Silk Robe". It is made in exactly the same way.<br><br><br><br>To make Ethereal Silk Swatches combine the following in a planar sowing kit:<br><br> - Strand of Ether x 2<br> - Ethereal Curing Agent (Celestial Essence x2, Soda, Paela Sap)<br><br><br>The Curing Agent is brewed in a Tanaan Brew Barrel. Both the brewing and tailoring combine require 220 modified skill. (Celestial Essences are brewed from a celestial temper and a research component.)<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(158); return false;'>Plane of Knowledge (PoK) mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(158); return false;'>Plane of Knowledge (PoK) quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/planes/planeofknowledge.html'>Plane of Knowledge (PoK) Map</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Keggylump</b> says:</i><br>if my memory serves me correctly, you cannot turn in ornate until level 55. (quest is marked 46-65)<br><br><i><b>Anidazen</b> says:</i><br>Ok, thanks for pointing that out. Will change it.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Doesn't Silk combine also require the Tanaan Sewing Needle as well?<br><br><i><b>Talerance</b> says:</i><br>I thank That doing this stuff would take lots of stuff you would need a group that would lut you loot all the stuff you whant so GL and P.S. i have the robe feet and the gloves. working on others<br><br><i><b>Restless</b> says:</i><br>Talerance ever heard of twinks?

Since the patterns are not no drop and swatches + patterns are sold in the bazaar, it actually takes very little to get your hands on Ornate..<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>are elemental patterns droppable?<br><br><i><b>Bislabus</b> says:</i><br>I currently have 3 elemental ornate pieces and 2 ornate pieces. Elemental ornate is NO DROP but is a whole lot better than ornate.  Elemental Ornate is dropped off of Elemental Planes/Time Minis(Elemental Pants are dropped off of EP+ Gods)You cannot obtain ornate till lvl 55 OR all of Tier 3 Flagged.  You cannot obtain elemental ornate till lvl 65 because it has a required lvl of 65.  You need to give Bor Warhammer 500plat to get a sewing kit + mage emblem.  Once you have your sewing kit,  put in the mage emblem, (new) Tanaan Sewing Needle(bought from vendors in PoK), ethereal silk swatche(s)(depends on the pattern:  Robe = 3 swatches, wrist = 1, gloves = 2, feet = 1, turban = 1) and the pattern itself.  Hope this helps.

-Bislabus
